In [[Pro Tools]] you can delete unused regions from your session either destructively or non destructively.


Go to '''Regions menu''' > '''Select''' > '''Unused''' 

This will select all the unused audio files in your session.


[[File:Pro Tools region select unused .png]]




Then go '''Region menu > Clear'''


[[File:Pro Tools region clear.png]]



A dialog box will appear asking if you wish to Remove or Delete the files.




[[File:Pro Tools Clear regions dialog box.png]]



Removing them simply removes them from your session. Deleting them removes them from the hard drive which  deletes them permanently.

